  "prompt": "How do I go about asking the right questions?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for asking effective questions:\n\n1. Be clear and specific\n- Know exactly what you want to learn\n- Avoid vague or overly broad questions\n\n2. Use open-ended questions\n- Encourage detailed responses\n- Start with \"how,\" \"what,\" \"why\"\n- Avoid yes/no questions\n\n3. Practice active listening\n- Pay attention to previous answers\n- Ask follow-up questions\n- Show genuine interest\n\n4. Do some background research first\n- Have context before asking\n- Demonstrate basic understanding\n- Ask more nuanced questions\n\n5. Consider the purpose of your question\n- Are you seeking information?\n- Looking for understanding?\n- Trying to solve a problem?\n\n6. Be curious and humble\n- Admit what you don't know\n- Show willingness to learn\n- Ask without judgment\n\n7. Consider the timing and setting\n- Choose appropriate moment\n- Be respectful of the person's time\n- Create comfortable environment\n\n8. Use different question techniques\n- Clarifying questions\n- Probing questions\n- Reflective questions\n\n9. Practice and refine\n- Learn from past interactions\n- Observe how others ask questions\n- Adjust your approach\n\nRemember, good questioning is a skill that improves with practice.",
